1
00:01:54,583 --> 00:02:01,583
[YOUNG LIA crying]

2
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:08,458
Here ya go.

3
00:02:09,875 --> 00:02:11,250
Oh, thank you.

4
00:02:13,875 --> 00:02:16,833
So tell me...
Did you pick it yourself?

5
00:02:21,916 --> 00:02:24,125
[NADJA] Lia... Wake up...

6
00:02:24,208 --> 00:02:25,416
Lia!

7
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:26,916
[LIA gasps]

8
00:02:30,458 --> 00:02:31,625
Nadja.

9
00:02:31,708 --> 00:02:33,000
Thank goodness...

10
00:02:33,083 --> 00:02:36,500
What a relief that you're
awake. Are you alright?

11
00:02:36,583 --> 00:02:39,416
[LIA wimpers]

12
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,125
[LIA] So... you saved me?

13
00:02:42,208 --> 00:02:43,625
I may be a
half-breed but I'm still

14
00:02:43,708 --> 00:02:45,666
a beastman through and through.

15
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,750
Saving you from
falling to your certain death

16
00:02:47,833 --> 00:02:50,875
was easy enough.
A piece of cake really.

17
00:02:50,958 --> 00:02:54,333
Well thank you.
I guess I owe you one.

18
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:56,958
[LIA and NADJA chuckle]

19
00:02:57,041 --> 00:02:58,875
[NADJA] I wonder what
the deal is with this cave?

20
00:02:58,958 --> 00:03:00,541
It's very peculiar.

21
00:03:00,625 --> 00:03:03,041
I'm glad we're out of
danger for the time being...

22
00:03:03,125 --> 00:03:06,333
but ever since I got in here
I've been experiencing visions.

23
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:09,250
I keep seeing distant
memories of people

24
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:11,208
long gone from my past.

25
00:03:11,291 --> 00:03:14,333
[LIA] That's because this
is the Labyrinth of Memories.

26
00:03:14,416 --> 00:03:17,583
I just saw a vision
of my own past as well.

27
00:03:17,666 --> 00:03:20,333
Something I had
forgotten about years ago.

28
00:03:26,416 --> 00:03:28,541
[SOLDIERS cock guns]

29
00:03:29,583 --> 00:03:31,500
[EAGLE MASTER] I'll be
taking the Destruct Code now

30
00:03:31,583 --> 00:03:33,500
so don't try anything stupid.

31
00:03:33,583 --> 00:03:34,708
Sorry,
we don't have it.

32
00:03:34,791 --> 00:03:36,208
She's telling
the truth, kuma.

33
00:03:36,291 --> 00:03:38,958
The Alligator Master stole
the Destruct Code for himself!

34
00:03:39,041 --> 00:03:41,083
He what?

35
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:43,000
Looks like the
Alligator Master betrayed

36
00:03:43,083 --> 00:03:45,333
the World Salvation
Committee as well.

37
00:03:50,208 --> 00:03:53,250
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] Don't listen
to what these peons have to say.

38
00:03:53,333 --> 00:03:56,250
It was you! Damn alligator.

39
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:59,416
If it's this that you
want it's yours; take it.

40
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:02,875
[EAGLE MASTER grunts]

41
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:05,000
In exchange I will
take the three members

42
00:04:05,083 --> 00:04:07,750
of the World Destruction
Committee into custody.

43
00:04:07,833 --> 00:04:10,166
[KYRIE shaky exhales]

44
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:12,041
[NADJA] Let me get this
straight. You're saying you

45
00:04:12,125 --> 00:04:14,833
met Kyrie over
three-hundred years ago?

46
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:16,750
[LIA] Right. It was
before I even reached

47
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:18,375
my hundredth birthday.

48
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:20,416
I'd been picking
flowers in Dragon Valley

49
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:22,416
and was heading
home for the day.

50
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:25,041
I'd been crying
because I fell.

51
00:04:25,125 --> 00:04:28,000
Kyrie had said some nice
things to cheer me up.

52
00:04:28,083 --> 00:04:31,875
But... he looked the
exact same as he does today.

53
00:04:31,958 --> 00:04:34,916
[LIA] Except...
his hair was different.

54
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,500
It was so red it looked
like it was on fire.

55
00:04:37,583 --> 00:04:40,041
So what exactly
does all that mean?

56
00:04:40,125 --> 00:04:42,500
That Kyrie hasn't
aged all these years?

57
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:45,625
Is it possible he's
a dragon like you?

58
00:04:45,708 --> 00:04:47,583
No way... If he were...

59
00:04:47,666 --> 00:04:50,416
I would have known he
was a dragon right away.

60
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,583
[NADJA] So if he's not, then...

61
00:04:52,666 --> 00:04:55,250
[LIA] He may be a creature
that lives as long as dragons,

62
00:04:55,333 --> 00:04:58,333
but as far as I know,
such a thing doesn't exist.

63
00:04:58,416 --> 00:05:00,791
[NADJA] Hm. Perhaps.

64
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:04,833
You know what?
We may have been

65
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:06,916
greatly mistaken about Kyrie.

66
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,583
[distant explosion]

67
00:05:14,125 --> 00:05:20,750
♪

68
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:22,208
Ahhh!

69
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:29,958
Huh...?

70
00:05:30,041 --> 00:05:31,583
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
Stop this futile resistance

71
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:34,375
and succumb to me quietly.
Or would you prefer to

72
00:05:34,458 --> 00:05:38,083
not learn about the
secrets of the Destruct Code?

73
00:05:38,166 --> 00:05:41,666
Secrets of the Destruct
Code? What do you know?

74
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:45,791
A lot. It seems your feeble
minds haven't grasped this yet.

75
00:05:45,875 --> 00:05:47,000
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] But
I have unlocked the hidden

76
00:05:47,083 --> 00:05:50,041
constructs that make
up the Destruct Code.

77
00:05:51,083 --> 00:05:53,750
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] Now...
come with me, human!

78
00:05:54,666 --> 00:05:56,041
Auhhh!

79
00:05:58,458 --> 00:05:59,333
[struggling]

80
00:05:59,416 --> 00:06:00,791
Toppy!

81
00:06:04,625 --> 00:06:06,083
[ALLIGATOR MASTER] Ugh!

82
00:06:07,958 --> 00:06:11,208
Morte! Lets go.
We're out of here, kuma!

83
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:13,416
We can't leave yet!
I'm not going anywhere

84
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:15,708
until I have the
Destruct Code back!

85
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:21,416
Hm-hm!

86
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:22,458
Huh?

87
00:06:22,541 --> 00:06:25,208
Do not let them get away!

88
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,583
I overheard the
Alligator Master.

89
00:06:31,666 --> 00:06:33,083
What's this about
him knowing secrets

90
00:06:33,166 --> 00:06:34,708
of the Destruct Code, kuma?

91
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:36,791
I don't know...
But if I had to guess,

92
00:06:36,875 --> 00:06:39,708
I'd say that the Destruct Code
Morte has on her right now

93
00:06:39,791 --> 00:06:41,750
isn't the real
thing, but a decoy!

94
00:06:41,833 --> 00:06:44,166
I hope you're wrong after
all we've been through!

95
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:46,000
Why else would he come
back with the same device

96
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:47,666
he had already
stolen from us?

97
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:50,750
It's the only thing that
makes sense. Think about it.

98
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:55,041
[MORTE] This is definitely
the real Destruct Code.

99
00:06:55,125 --> 00:06:57,041
I know it is, I can feel it!

100
00:06:58,125 --> 00:07:00,833
Now that we're back inside
the Labyrinth of Memories,

101
00:07:00,916 --> 00:07:03,083
if I can conjure
up that memory again,

102
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:05,291
I might be able
to figure this out!

103
00:07:05,375 --> 00:07:07,750
What do you mean by
"that memory," kuma?

104
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,416
[KYRIE] The memory I
had of Morte's brother

105
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:11,166
getting the Destruct Code!

106
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:12,708
[MORTE] Huh? Wait,
you mean to tell me

107
00:07:12,791 --> 00:07:15,333
that you were there the
day my brother, Reve, died?

108
00:07:15,416 --> 00:07:17,083
Yes, no. Maybe. I don't know.

109
00:07:17,166 --> 00:07:19,125
The thing is I can't
actually remember any of it.

110
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:21,416
I'm not even sure
if I was really there.

111
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:22,708
In fact, I'm not sure any of it

112
00:07:22,791 --> 00:07:25,666
actually happened
or not. It's confusing.

113
00:07:28,375 --> 00:07:30,041
Huh?

114
00:07:30,125 --> 00:07:31,916
Eghhh! Gimme that!

115
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,333
[KYRIE] Uh...

116
00:07:35,416 --> 00:07:36,541
[MORTE] Aughhh!

117
00:07:36,625 --> 00:07:38,000
[KYRIE and TOPPY] Ahhh!

118
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,791
[BOTH gasp]

119
00:07:45,458 --> 00:07:50,708
[KYRIE screams]

120
00:07:57,708 --> 00:07:59,208
[GOLDEN LION A] The
beastmen are attacking!

121
00:07:59,291 --> 00:08:01,291
[GOLDEN LION B]
Grab your weapons!

122
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:13,375
♪

123
00:08:23,166 --> 00:08:25,041
Kyrie!

124
00:08:25,125 --> 00:08:26,500
Reve?

125
00:08:34,041 --> 00:08:35,625
What are you still doing here?

126
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:38,500
I thought you were supposed
to leave for Tomai by now.

127
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:41,208
It would have been a
pointless trip anyway.

128
00:08:41,291 --> 00:08:44,458
So I figured, what's
the rush, ya know?

129
00:08:44,541 --> 00:08:46,958
What the heck has
gotten into you, Kyrie?

130
00:08:47,041 --> 00:08:48,500
I just wanted to
find out whether or not

131
00:08:48,583 --> 00:08:51,250
you guys would really
be able to save the world.

132
00:08:51,333 --> 00:08:52,666
I just got curious.

133
00:08:52,750 --> 00:08:54,416
[REVE] Forget all that,
it's dangerous here!

134
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,916
The beastmen found us,
so you better find

135
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,416
a good place to hide!

136
00:08:58,583 --> 00:09:00,083
[KYRIE] Uh...!

137
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,916
Who exactly are you?

138
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:07,375
[KYRIE RED sighs]

139
00:09:07,458 --> 00:09:10,208
So you still can't remember?

140
00:09:10,291 --> 00:09:14,125
Then in that case...
I'll just tell you.

141
00:09:14,208 --> 00:09:16,166
[KYRIE RED] That black orb
Morte's been carrying around

142
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:19,000
all this time...
isn't the Destruct Code.

143
00:09:20,416 --> 00:09:22,916
The real Destruct
Code is inside of...

144
00:09:23,750 --> 00:09:25,125
[KYRIE gasping]

145
00:09:28,791 --> 00:09:30,833
[groans]

146
00:09:33,625 --> 00:09:35,833
Morte! Wake up, kuma!

147
00:09:39,541 --> 00:09:41,000
Where are we?

148
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:42,833
[motorized door opens]

149
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:45,916
[EAGLE MASTER] It's
about time you woke up.

150
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:48,291
[TOPPY] Where is Kyrie, kuma?!

151
00:09:48,375 --> 00:09:50,666
[EAGLE MASTER] How should
I know? He's probably buried

152
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:52,375
under the rubble in that cave.

153
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:54,250
And if he's still
alive, he's reveling in

154
00:09:54,333 --> 00:09:56,583
the memories of
his happier days.

155
00:09:56,666 --> 00:09:57,875
Now listen...

156
00:09:57,958 --> 00:10:00,250
I need to ask you
something important.

157
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:03,375
What did he mean by the
secrets of the Destruct Code?

158
00:10:03,458 --> 00:10:05,708
[EAGLE MASTER] What's does
the Alligator Master know?

159
00:10:05,791 --> 00:10:08,333
How are you supposed
to use this thing?

160
00:10:08,416 --> 00:10:09,666
[MORTE] Hmph.

161
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:12,333
I already told
you, I don't know.

162
00:10:12,416 --> 00:10:13,875
[EAGLE MASTER grunts]

163
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:16,708
In that case, I'll have
to force it out of you!

164
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:20,666
[TOPPY] No! Don't do it, kuma!

165
00:10:39,166 --> 00:10:43,083
[KYRIE groaning]

166
00:10:43,166 --> 00:10:53,125
♪

167
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,833
[water drop]

168
00:11:10,791 --> 00:11:14,791
[water dripping]

169
00:11:14,875 --> 00:11:18,916
[water sloshing]

170
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:42,291
What is it, Lia?
What's wrong?

171
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,583
[LIA] Kyrie...?

172
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,250
I need to ask you...

173
00:11:53,333 --> 00:11:56,166
Is it possible that
you could be the...

174
00:11:56,250 --> 00:11:58,833
[NADJA] Um... I don't
know how to put this...

175
00:11:58,916 --> 00:12:00,291
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
Your hunch is right.

176
00:12:00,375 --> 00:12:02,375
He is the Destruct Code.

177
00:12:02,458 --> 00:12:03,833
[BOTH gasp]

178
00:12:06,625 --> 00:12:10,125
Yes, it took me quite a
while to figure that out.

179
00:12:10,208 --> 00:12:12,208
[KYRIE] What did you
do with Morte and Toppy?

180
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:13,666
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
They're spending some time

181
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:16,291
with the Eagle Master.
And right now those

182
00:12:16,375 --> 00:12:19,208
World Salvation Committee
dimwits are trying to

183
00:12:19,291 --> 00:12:21,541
get the girl to confess
all the hidden secrets of

184
00:12:21,625 --> 00:12:23,833
the Destruct Code,
even though the real one

185
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:26,458
is standing right
in front of me.

186
00:12:27,958 --> 00:12:30,333
Now... time to come with me.

187
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:32,916
And we will create
a new world together.

188
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,375
Huh?

189
00:12:34,458 --> 00:12:36,791
Not quite. Before
we figure out what to do

190
00:12:36,875 --> 00:12:39,041
with the Destruct Code...
there's the matter of

191
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:41,916
payback for what
happened to us before.

192
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,750
[ALLIGATOR MASTER]
How dare you stand in my way!

193
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:48,166
[LIA] If I'm not mistaken,
it was you who betrayed us.

194
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:52,000
Now get over here, you fool!

195
00:12:52,083 --> 00:12:57,541
[LIA and ALLIGATOR
MASTER screaming]

196
00:12:57,625 --> 00:12:59,416
Good grief...

197
00:12:59,500 --> 00:13:00,875
So, Kyrie...

198
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:06,416
[LIA and ALLIGATOR
MASTER screaming]

199
00:13:09,291 --> 00:13:11,208
[distant crash]

200
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:12,916
[WSC SOLDIERS] Huh...?

201
00:13:15,458 --> 00:13:17,250
Kuma?

202
00:13:17,333 --> 00:13:20,333
[EAGLE MASTER] Now... perhaps
this will jog your memory.

203
00:13:20,416 --> 00:13:21,291
[MORTE] Fine then...

204
00:13:21,375 --> 00:13:23,958
But I said before, I don't know!

205
00:13:24,041 --> 00:13:26,458
Heh. Alright,
have it your way.

206
00:13:26,541 --> 00:13:28,166
I prefer it, because
the longer it takes

207
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:31,041
for you to answer,
the more fun I'll have.

208
00:13:33,625 --> 00:13:35,000
[WSC SOLDIERS] Ahhh!

209
00:13:35,083 --> 00:13:36,000
[EAGLE MASTER] What the...?

210
00:13:36,083 --> 00:13:37,875
[WSC SOLDIER] Ahhh!

211
00:13:37,958 --> 00:13:39,666
What's going on?!

212
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:47,291
[ALL] Huh?

213
00:13:52,375 --> 00:13:53,250
Huh?

214
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:54,708
How did you get in here?!

215
00:13:54,791 --> 00:13:56,500
[EAGLE MASTER power yell]

216
00:14:02,208 --> 00:14:03,916
Kyrie.

217
00:14:04,458 --> 00:14:06,166
[KYRIE] Are you two alright?

218
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:10,416
Kyrie... your hair...
How'd you dye it, kuma?

219
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,625
We'll chat later.
Right now you need to

220
00:14:12,708 --> 00:14:15,208
find a way outta here
as soon as you can.

221
00:14:15,291 --> 00:14:16,958
What? Wait a minute.

222
00:14:17,041 --> 00:14:18,166
[MORTE] The Destruct Code is...

223
00:14:18,250 --> 00:14:19,541
[KYRIE] Morte.

224
00:14:20,458 --> 00:14:21,750
Don't worry about it.

225
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:24,041
It's not what
you think it is.

226
00:14:25,083 --> 00:14:27,291
What are you
talking about, kuma?

227
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,708
This ball is not
the Destruct Code.

228
00:14:31,791 --> 00:14:35,166
It's really nothing more
than a storage device.

229
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:36,875
It may be hard to believe...

230
00:14:36,958 --> 00:14:38,791
but I am the Destruct Code.

231
00:14:38,875 --> 00:14:40,083
Huh?

232
00:14:40,166 --> 00:14:42,000
Are you serious, kuma?!

233
00:14:42,083 --> 00:14:43,583
I don't understand.

234
00:14:44,541 --> 00:14:46,541
[KYRIE] During my days
spent traveling the world,

235
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:49,250
I once visited
the Golden Lions camp.

236
00:14:49,333 --> 00:14:51,125
That is where I
met your brother.

237
00:14:51,208 --> 00:14:53,416
When he told you he had
found the Destruct Code,

238
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:55,750
he wasn't referring to the orb.

239
00:14:57,125 --> 00:14:59,458
[KYRIE] He was talking
about having met me.

240
00:15:00,625 --> 00:15:02,500
[KYRIE] I got caught
up in the ensuing battle

241
00:15:02,583 --> 00:15:04,750
and ended up losing the orb.

242
00:15:06,125 --> 00:15:08,583
[KYRIE] That is how it
ended up in Reve's coffin...

243
00:15:08,666 --> 00:15:11,875
and eventually found
its way to your hands.

244
00:15:13,541 --> 00:15:15,291
[KYRIE] Having
lost every trace of memory

245
00:15:15,375 --> 00:15:16,916
as to who I was...

246
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:20,625
I headed for Tomai as
plain ol'... Kyrie Ilnis.

247
00:15:22,166 --> 00:15:23,625
[KYRIE] Shortly thereafter...

248
00:15:23,708 --> 00:15:26,125
I met you, Morte.

249
00:15:26,208 --> 00:15:27,791
[MORTE] That's nuts...

250
00:15:29,958 --> 00:15:31,416
[MORTE] What is this?

251
00:15:32,541 --> 00:15:34,708
[KYRIE] These
are my true memories.

252
00:15:34,791 --> 00:15:38,166
I've walked this planet since
its first day of creation...

253
00:15:38,250 --> 00:15:40,458
tens of thousands of years.

254
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:43,041
These are the
memories I take with me.

255
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:49,333
So then... if you're
the Destruct Code...

256
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:53,125
That means you have the
power to destroy everything?

257
00:15:53,208 --> 00:15:55,833
Destruct should not
be taken literally...

258
00:15:55,916 --> 00:15:59,541
I've been here since the
very beginning of existence,

259
00:15:59,625 --> 00:16:03,000
allowing me the
power to reset the world.

260
00:16:03,750 --> 00:16:06,083
[KYRIE] Whenever someone
comes along who truly believes

261
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:08,416
in the Destruct Code
and would like nothing more

262
00:16:08,500 --> 00:16:10,583
than to see the world go away,

263
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:13,250
that's when my power activates.

264
00:16:16,916 --> 00:16:18,458
That man is the Destruct Code.

265
00:16:18,541 --> 00:16:20,791
Take him into custody, alive!

266
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:25,041
[WSC SOLDIERS grunting]

267
00:16:26,375 --> 00:16:27,750
Kyrie...

268
00:16:28,666 --> 00:16:30,958
[WSC SOLDIERS yell]

269
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:39,708
[EAGLE MASTER] Aaahhh!

270
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:41,875
Say goodbye, freak!

271
00:16:41,958 --> 00:16:43,708
[gasps]

272
00:16:44,583 --> 00:16:46,250
[EAGLE MASTER]
Heh, heh, heh... Ahhh...

273
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:47,833
No wait... Please, don't!

274
00:16:47,916 --> 00:16:49,958
Ahhh!

275
00:16:51,875 --> 00:16:53,250
Amazing...

276
00:16:53,333 --> 00:16:55,125
He is the Destruct Code!

277
00:16:55,208 --> 00:16:58,250
We're finally seeing
Kyrie's true power, kuma!

278
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:01,708
[KYRIE] When someone hopes
for it strongly enough,

279
00:17:01,791 --> 00:17:04,250
the Destruct Code
becomes active.

280
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:06,083
Morte believed
in the existence of

281
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:07,833
the code from the beginning...

282
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:11,416
and truly wished
for world destruction.

283
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:20,375
And ever since that day...

284
00:17:20,458 --> 00:17:22,041
the Destruct
Code has been active

285
00:17:22,125 --> 00:17:24,000
and awaiting instructions.

286
00:17:27,041 --> 00:17:28,416
[TOPPY] Wait, not yet, kuma!

287
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:29,958
[MORTE] Kyrie!

288
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:33,708
[BOTH gasp]

289
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:39,125
[NADJA] This must be it...

290
00:17:39,208 --> 00:17:41,875
We are looking upon the
power of the Destruct Code!

291
00:17:44,083 --> 00:17:46,250
[LIA] Watch out! Nadja!

292
00:17:48,416 --> 00:17:50,625
[TOPPY] Kyrie! Stop this, kuma!

293
00:17:52,041 --> 00:17:53,666
Kyrie...

294
00:17:54,041 --> 00:17:55,458
[AGAN] Hey!

295
00:17:57,291 --> 00:17:58,541
[TOPPY] Agan?

296
00:17:58,625 --> 00:18:00,000
I'm trying to deliver some food

297
00:18:00,083 --> 00:18:01,625
and this is what I come across?

298
00:18:01,708 --> 00:18:03,750
What the hell have
you guys done now?!

299
00:18:04,583 --> 00:18:06,041
You again!

300
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:08,333
[AGAN] If you wanna ride
with me, you've gotta pay up!

301
00:18:08,416 --> 00:18:10,083
[TOPPY] This is not
the time to be haggling.

302
00:18:10,166 --> 00:18:12,166
Now hurry up
and let us on, kuma!

303
00:18:14,291 --> 00:18:16,166
[PEOPLE screaming]

304
00:18:18,250 --> 00:18:20,458
[MORTE] If we don't put a stop
to this soon, the entire world

305
00:18:20,541 --> 00:18:23,208
will be reset into
nothing but a sea of sand!

306
00:18:23,291 --> 00:18:26,500
Isn't that what you've
been wishing for all along?

307
00:18:26,583 --> 00:18:28,750
[MORTE] Is it?

308
00:18:28,833 --> 00:18:31,333
Is this the world I wished for?

309
00:18:31,416 --> 00:18:32,791
♪

310
00:18:43,208 --> 00:18:44,708
[MORTE] Kyrie.

311
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,041
Morte!

312
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:48,833
[TOPPY] Morte!

313
00:18:55,083 --> 00:18:57,250
[MORTE heavy breathing]

314
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:03,375
[MORTE] I activated
the Destruct Code.

315
00:19:03,458 --> 00:19:06,666
No, I activated Kyrie.

316
00:19:10,083 --> 00:19:12,666
[MORTE] But is this
the outcome I want?

317
00:19:13,500 --> 00:19:16,500
[MORTE] Do I really
want the world to end?

318
00:19:19,875 --> 00:19:21,333
[MORTE gasps]

319
00:19:24,500 --> 00:19:27,625
[MORTE'S DAD] The world
is constantly changing.

320
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:30,583
Now it's your turn to
try to change the world.

321
00:19:30,666 --> 00:19:32,500
And you will.

322
00:19:32,583 --> 00:19:35,083
Go create a
new future, sweetheart.

323
00:19:35,166 --> 00:19:38,375
One where everybody
in the world can be happy.

324
00:19:38,458 --> 00:19:39,916
[REVE] But I feel a whole
lot better knowing you're

325
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:44,208
not alone anymore. I'm so
happy that you're doing okay.

326
00:19:45,583 --> 00:19:56,291
[MORTE crying]

327
00:19:59,208 --> 00:20:00,750
[MORTE] Enough.

328
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:03,375
The world doesn't have to end.

329
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:10,291
It's fine just the way it is.

330
00:20:13,041 --> 00:20:14,333
[MORTE] The world is what it is

331
00:20:14,416 --> 00:20:17,291
and I have no
right to destroy it.

332
00:20:19,583 --> 00:20:22,125
[MORTE] So please...

333
00:20:22,208 --> 00:20:23,833
stop this.

334
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:49,625
[MORTE moans]

335
00:20:49,708 --> 00:20:51,166
Kyrie?

336
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,833
Huh...?

337
00:20:52,916 --> 00:20:54,250
Morte.

338
00:20:54,333 --> 00:21:04,291
♪

339
00:21:08,458 --> 00:21:10,333
[TOPPY] When the gods
created the world...

340
00:21:10,416 --> 00:21:12,416
they also designed
a Destruct Code

341
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:14,958
capable of bringing
the world to ruin.

342
00:21:15,041 --> 00:21:17,166
They did this so that
if someone believed in

343
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:19,250
the existence of
the Destruct Code,

344
00:21:19,333 --> 00:21:21,458
and wished to the very
core of their being for

345
00:21:21,541 --> 00:21:24,416
the world to end, the
code would be activated,

346
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:27,416
resetting time and
space to it's beginnings.

347
00:21:27,500 --> 00:21:29,958
The gods gave both
humans and beastmen alike

348
00:21:30,041 --> 00:21:33,666
this special power,
to do with as they please.

349
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:36,625
And so... the world was saved.

350
00:21:36,708 --> 00:21:40,125
However, that does not mean
the world had changed at all.

351
00:21:40,208 --> 00:21:43,208
A small yet privileged class
of beastmen still controlled

352
00:21:43,291 --> 00:21:45,208
nearly all the
wealth in the land,

353
00:21:45,291 --> 00:21:47,875
and humanity
was still oppressed.

354
00:21:47,958 --> 00:21:50,125
The Destruct Code
does not possess the power

355
00:21:50,208 --> 00:21:53,875
to change the world.
Instead, we are the ones

356
00:21:53,958 --> 00:21:56,041
who can bring
change to the world.

357
00:21:56,916 --> 00:21:59,041
[TOPPY] There are
two kinds of futures.

358
00:21:59,125 --> 00:22:01,791
A bright, shining
future full of promise,

359
00:22:01,875 --> 00:22:04,666
and a future under
a veil of darkness.

360
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:07,083
But if a future of
darkness is upon us,

361
00:22:07,166 --> 00:22:12,250
there is nothing to fear, for
hope exists in both futures.

362
00:22:12,333 --> 00:22:14,708
Because the future
continually changes through

363
00:22:14,791 --> 00:22:16,666
the hope of those individuals

364
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:19,500
brave enough to bring
about that change.

365
00:22:19,583 --> 00:22:21,041
[TOPPY] Kuma.

366
00:22:21,958 --> 00:22:23,333
Hey!

367
00:22:23,416 --> 00:22:26,458
Look at you. A cute little
bear trying to act all cool.

368
00:22:26,541 --> 00:22:28,500
[TOPPY] Don't
call me bear, kuma!

369
00:22:28,583 --> 00:22:30,208
[BOTH laughing]

